Class HITDataReader

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
HITDataInput
Deprecated. 

@Deprecated
public class HITDataReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements HITDataInput

The HITDataReader class provides a structured way to access HIT data stored in a file. It assumes that the data is stored essentially as a table with rows and columns. The top row is assumed to be field names, and the rows below it are data.
